  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The hemolysis accumulation model employs the power-law Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation, which is theoretically valid under the assumption that red blood cell damage accumulates linearly with exposure time and that the stress-exposure relationship is stationary across the operating envelope. This linearity assumption was verified at the nominal operating point (3.5 L/min, 2400 RPM) against in-vitro hemolysis data, but the package does not include a validation result confirming that the linearity precondition holds across the full five-point flow-speed matrix (2.0–5.0 L/min, 1800–3000 RPM) that constitutes the COU.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
