      "name": "Nominal-point hemolysis correlation validation (3.5 L/min, 2400 RPM)",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (nIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at the nominal CPB operating point. Predicted nIH = 0.0043 g/100 L versus measured 0.0047 g/100 L (8.5% relative error). Acceptance criterion of ±15% met. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law accumulation model performs adequately at this single operating condition, consistent with the linearity assumption at low-shear steady-state flow. No multi-point sweep validation is included.",
      "outcome": "Passed",
